§I CONTEXT-NOTE @ proto-infra-already-exists
  ‼ baseline dd59670 contains the cssl-test-verifier crate (manifest + JSONL verifier)
    PLUS cssl-rt fs_event_jsonl emitting process.start / loa_startup.ctor / process.exit
    + per-FFI EventScope traces from host_audio/gpu/input/thread/time/window/http
  ‼ this work EXTENDS that infra to satisfy A05.1·A05.2·A05.3 contract · it does NOT
    rebuild from scratch
  ‼ ¬ duplicate-EventScope · ¬ alt-JSONL-format · ¬ parallel-verifier-crate

§I HYPOTHESIS-TO-FALSIFY
  H · the existing cssl-test-verifier crate's manifest schema can be extended to express
       "this test must produce ≥1 observable side-effect" and the test-runner can be
       wired to FAIL exit=0 + stdout=∅ + stderr=∅ + zero-fs-mutation tests

§I FAILURE-MODE-ENUMERATION
  FM.1 · current verifier consumes JSONL · "no observable effect" needs detection in
         the verifier · what counts as "observable"?
         options : (a) any cssl_events.jsonl entry counts · (b) explicit
                   cssl_test_observe(...) registration · (c) fs/stdout/stderr-mutation
                   detection by external watcher
         spec-70 A05.2 prescribes (b) explicitly · use it
         A05.1 prescribes (c) for the GATE itself · so combine : pass iff (b) ∨ (c)

  FM.2 · benchmark tests intentionally measure idle (CPU-only · no fs)
         spec-70 OQ.03 default : bench tests register cssl_test_observe(BENCH_FLAG)
         ⇒ implementation : provide cssl_test_observe(name : &str) macro/intrinsic
                            that emits a JSONL entry with kind=test.observe.{name}

  FM.3 · stdlib has implicit fs/stdout writes (e.g. cssl-rt logger init)
         these would falsely pass A05.1 even for empty user_main
         mitigation : test-runner filters JSONL · counts only non-rt-internal kinds
                      OR : A05.3 golden-test (empty user_main) explicitly tests this case

  FM.4 · race : test exits before JSONL flush · verifier sees empty file
         existing fs_event_jsonl uses %TEMP%\cssl_events.jsonl · need flush-on-exit
         (loa_startup.shutdown_hook should fsync · verify in code)

  FM.5 · CI parallel-test runs collide on shared %TEMP%\cssl_events.jsonl
         mitigation : per-test-PID-or-UUID JSONL path

§I CHEAPEST-FALSIFICATION
  write golden-test : examples/empty_user_main.cssl with `fn user_main() {}`
  run via test-runner · expect FAIL with diagnostic
    "test produced no observable effect (A05.1 violation)"
  if it PASSES · gate is broken or not wired
  ⇒ ~5 LOC test · highest-signal

